# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0
# Adjustfile — Drift-tolerance contract for Cliodynamics.jl
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell <j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>
#
# Cumulative-drift catchment: tolerance bands + corrective actions.
# Authority: advisory (Yard) — continue-with-warnings; auto_fix where deterministic.
# Run with: adjust check    Fix with: adjust fix
#
# NOTE (2026-06-13): rewritten for Cliodynamics.jl. The estate-carried file was the
# rsr-template-repo Adjustfile (drift checks about "template placeholders").

@abstract:
Drift tolerances and corrective actions for Cliodynamics.jl. Unlike MUST (hard
gate), ADJUST tracks cumulative drift against tolerance bands and proposes
corrective actions. Advisory — it warns and trends, it does not block.
@end

## Metadata Drift

### state-currency
- description: 6a2/STATE.a2ml last-updated should track real activity
- tolerance: last-updated within ~30 days of the most recent feature commit
- corrective: refresh .machine_readable/6a2/STATE.a2ml (version snapshot + test count)
- severity: advisory

### version-sync
- description: version in 6a2/STATE.a2ml should match Project.toml
- tolerance: 0 version-field mismatches between STATE.a2ml and Project.toml
- corrective: update STATE.a2ml [metadata] version to match Project.toml
- severity: advisory

## Governance Drift

### no-template-identity-leak
- description: contractiles must describe Cliodynamics.jl, not rsr-template-repo
- tolerance: 0 contractiles claiming to be the canonical template
- corrective: substitute repo identity; rewrite template-role prose for this repo
- severity: advisory
- notes: the estate flat-contractile set shipped un-substituted (see Mustfile/Intentfile/Trustfile headers); upstream template fix tracked separately

### contractile-completeness
- description: all six flat contractiles + Justfile present
- tolerance: Adjust/Bust/Dust/Intent/Must/Trust .a2ml + Justfile all exist
- corrective: add the missing contractile
- severity: advisory

## Code & Test Drift

### test-baseline
- description: test count should not silently regress below the documented baseline
- tolerance: ">= 124 tests passing across 18 testsets"
- corrective: investigate dropped/disabled tests before merge
- severity: advisory
- notes: CLAUDE.md documents 124 tests / 18 testsets; verify against test/runtests.jl

### testset-completeness
- description: all 34 exported functions have at least one test
- tolerance: 0 exported functions without a corresponding @testset
- corrective: add @testset in test/runtests.jl for the missing function
- severity: advisory

## Hygiene Drift

### spdx-header-consistency
- description: all source files carry an SPDX-License-Identifier
- tolerance: 0 files missing SPDX headers
- corrective: add MPL-2.0 SPDX headers (the estate REUSE sweep covers the bulk)
- severity: advisory

### no-template-identity-leak-band
- description: no contractile file still carries rsr-template-repo as identity
- tolerance: 0 such files (this was found and fixed 2026-06-13)
- corrective: rewrite the offending contractile for this repo
- severity: advisory
- notes: Adjustfile/Intentfile/Mustfile/Trustfile were all template-leaked; rewritten 2026-06-13
